HEADWORD: callathump
<hw>callathump</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a noisy boisterous
parade.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> callithump, callithump parade.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a noisy mock serenade (made by banging pans and
kettles) to a newly married couple.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> shivaree, chivaree, charivari, callithump.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

